  "text": "To speedup the computational time of the exponentials used in (7), the MIPP wrapper [CITATION_1] has been used. MIPP proposes a vectorized implementation of the exponential based on a series expansion. Many intrinsic functions are encapsulated to compute the exponential. MIPP also allows to write portable intrinsic codes. A single SIMD code is written for multiple ISAs such as SSE, NEON, AVX, AVX512 and KNCI thanks to the meta-programming techniques.",
